text: P. C. C. & St. L. Railroad Freight Depot, also known as the Central Union Warehouse, was a historic freight depot located at Indianapolis, Marion County, Indiana. It was built in 1916 by the Pittsburgh, Cincinnati, Chicago and St. Louis Railroad. It was a one-story, brick warehouse building measuring 790 feet long and 70 feet wide. Note: This includes It has been demolished. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1995 and delisted in 1997. ==References== Category:Former National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Railway stations on the National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1916 Category:Buildings and structures in Indianapolis Category:National Register of Historic Places in Indianapolis Category:Transportation buildings and structures in Marion County, Indiana
